<br>
In fact, the reason we have not added another guild at this time is the lack of unity (or rather everyone seemingly abstaining) for one choice.<br>
<br>
So... what needs to happen for &quot;someone to make a decision&quot;??? In this thread name who you would like to see added, and why. Over 10 different guildnames have been brought up at one time or another. To differentiate these guilds we need our members to make some choices on who they would like to see join us.<br>
<br>
I had asked that this be discussed on your boards with your members and a decision be brought back here. I haven't seen any decisions from any of the 4 guilds, so let's move that discussion here.<br>
<br>
What will happen? We will invite the selected guilds to join us on a few of our raids to be sure they are what we expected them to be. At that time they will be invited.<br>
<br>
Bamil Banebringer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvainne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vainne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/01 3:11:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http--braggarts.shareplay.com-pics-Wythe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> I speak strongly FOR VC, Issu and Daywalkers, having grouped with several of their members during their formative years. In addition, I'd like to see Bethene's guild (whatever they are called) join the SGA.<br>
<br>
As with any guild, not every single person in them, (or in SF, SG, Amnesty, etc) is my favorite---I only mention this because Holt, please have a caution before dismissing one guild out of hand. Whatever your slight was, I recommend reconciling it between yourself and the party involved. <br>
<br>
The arguement against adding more members due to lack of coherency is a strong one, I agree. Except, this is the thing: at its core the SGA offers the possibility to do something small guilds cannot do on their own---that is, raid. This idea is bound to be popular.<br>
<br>
As long as any guild maintains the respect and loot rules set forth by the SGA, I would hope that their members would be included.<br>
<br>
If adding more bodies makes more work, then we need to set up procedures to streamline this. Database with member lists, Periodic meetings between guild officials, a prodedure for greivances, etc, etc. Not everyone in all of these guilds will use the SGA. For those that do (and may all they be enchanters and clerics :P) set up strict guidleines and there shouldnt be any problems. <p><b> ~The Nightblind Bard~
<b>~Amnesty, Saryrn~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6A74B4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulandyalexandre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LandyAlexandre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/1/01 6:56:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Guilds</span><hr size=1> I have grouped with numerous members and officers of the Valiant Coalition (VC) guild and was almost always pleasantly surprised with the quality of these players.  For this reason i was earnestly looking forward to the possibility of having them added to the SGA... <br>
<br>
However it would seem that the last few weeks have not been kind to VC.  Apparently, this guild may be about to disband after a failed attempt to ally/merge with Travellers of Norrath.  I have been told that their GL left the guild recently.  I know for a fact that Elian, the officer who initially signaled their interest in the SGA is no longer with them.  <br>
<br>
It is unfortunate that this happened to VC, but it does bring out the point that crafting an alliance can put a guild under stress.  If this past weekend's hate raid is any meaure of success, it seems clear that the SGA has been a real boon to our guilds' memberships.  Personally, I greatly enjoy the company of my SGA brethren, so feel i must urge that we proceed with care.  It would be a tremendous shame to have our attempts to expand the SGA lead to its reduction or demise.  <br>
<br>
Landy Alexandre<br>
